abs(int128).notice: Get the absolute value of a real. Just the same as abs on a normal int128.

atan2(int128,int128).notice: Compute the nice two-component arctangent of y/x.

atanSmall(int128).notice: Calculate atan(x) for x in [-1, 1]. Uses the Chebyshev polynomial approach presented at https://www.mathworks.com/help/fixedpoint/examples/calculate-fixed-point-arctangent.html Uses polynomials received by personal communication. 0.999974x-0.332568x^3+0.193235x^5-0.115729x^7+0.0519505x^9-0.0114658x^11

div(int128,int128).notice: Divide one real by another real. Truncates overflows.

exp(int128).notice: Calculate e^x with a sensible maximum iteration count to wait until convergence. Note that it is potentially possible to get an un-converged value; lack of convergence does not throw.

expLimited(int128,int256).notice: Calculate e^x. Uses the series given at <http://pages.mtu.edu/~shene/COURSES/cs201/NOTES/chap04/exp.html>.     * Lets you artificially limit the number of iterations.     * Note that it is potentially possible to get an un-converged value; lack of convergence does not throw.

fpart(int128).notice: Get the fractional part of a real, as a real. Ignores sign (so fpart(-0.5) is 0.5).

fpartSigned(int128).notice: Get the fractional part of a real, as a real. Respects sign (so fpartSigned(-0.5) is -0.5).

fraction(int88,int88).notice: Create a real from a rational fraction.

fractionalBits(int128).notice: Returns the fractional bits of a real. Ignores the sign of the real.

fromReal(int128).notice: Convert a real to an integer. Preserves sign.

ipart(int128).notice: Get the integer part of a fixed point value.

ipow(int128,int88).notice: Raise a number to a positive integer power in O(log power) time. See <https://stackoverflow.com/a/101613>

ln(int128).notice: Calculate a natural logarithm with a sensible maximum iteration count to wait until convergence. Note that it is potentially possible to get an un-converged value; lack of convergence does not throw.

lnLimited(int128,int256).notice: Calculate the natural log of a number. Rescales the input value and uses the algorithm outlined at <https://math.stackexchange.com/a/977836> and the ipow implementation.     * Lets you artificially limit the number of iterations.     * Note that it is potentially possible to get an un-converged value; lack of convergence does not throw.

mul(int128,int128).notice: Multiply one real by another. Truncates overflows.

pow(int128,int128).notice: Raise any number to any power, except for negative bases to fractional powers.

round(int128).notice: Round a real to the nearest integral real value.

sin(int128).notice: Calculate sin(x) with a sensible maximum iteration count to wait until convergence.

sinLimited(int128,int88).notice: Compute the sin of a number to a certain number of Taylor series terms.

sqrt(int128).notice: Compute the square root of a number.

tan(int128).notice: Calculate tan(x). May overflow for large results. May throw if tan(x) would be infinite, or return an approximation, or overflow.

toReal(int88).notice: Convert an integer to a real. Preserves sign.
